This paper deals with the online metric bipartite matching problem, which is a problem in algorithmic game theory and optimization. The problem involves matching requests to servers in a metric space, and the analysis involves competitive ratios and worst-case analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AL (Computational Geometry), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
